The paper discusses the vulnerability of machine learning models to extraction attacks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on the estimation of information leakage in such attacks, which involves probabilistic modeling and Bayesian networks, indicating a strong connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The applications of machine learning models in multimedia also suggest a possible connection to computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the use of a theoretical framework to measure information leakage may also relate to social and information networks (cs.SI).
